				<p><p>There are an increasing number of sites on Stack Exchange for other languages. Ask Different is an English site and as such all posts should be in English.</p>

<ul>
<li>When a post is solely in a different language, it should be translated to English. The post should then be dealt with as usual.</li>
<li>When a translation to a different language is given such as that in the linked answer, the different language should be edited out.</li>
